text:
I'm about half an hour into this, and it seems Gura lack a basic understanding of how this game works.  The game is based on forced perspective, which allows you to change the size of objects.  When you pick up an item, you're not actually holding it.  You're locking its size relative to your camera view.  Then, when you let go of it, it's raycasted out into the environment as far as it can go without running into something, and then its size changes based on how far away you are.  When you put something far away, it gets bigger so that it maintains its apparent size to your camera.  When you put something close, it gets smaller to maintain its apparent size.
Gura is talking about throwing, which isn't a thing because you're not actually grabbing objects.  If you want something put somewhere, you move your camera so that the object looks like it is where you want it, and then when you let go of it, it will be there.
